The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, May 28: Swiss drug firm Novartis AG today sweetened its open offer price to Rs 450 a share from the original offer of Rs 351 a piece to acquire an additional 39 per cent stake in its Indian subsidiary, Novartis India. In March, Novartis AG had said it would make an open offer for a further 1,24,64,710 shares or 39 per cent stake in its Indian subsidiary, at a price of Rs 351 per share.                             
	 Amritsar, May 28: Bharti Wal-Mart will open its first cash-and-carry store in the country on Saturday in the city. The company had earlier planned to open the store on May 26. The plan was deferred following the outbreak of violence in the state, protesting the killing of a Dera leader in Austria.                            
	 New Delhi, May 28: Insurance regulator IRDA has asked life insurance companies not to deduct any premium while returning the money to the customer who wants to cancel the policy within 15 days of opting for it.                            
	 New Delhi, May 28: Inflation remained unchanged at 0.61 per cent for the week ended May 16 compared with the previous week. Inflation stood at 8.66 per cent during the same week a year ago.                            
	 Berlin/ Detroit, May 28: General Motors said today it reached a deal with some major bondholders that will give them a bigger stake in a reorganised auto maker and could pave the way for a fast-track bankruptcy backed by the US treasury.                                                                                                                            
